ENCLOSURE GREATER THAN 1" (25mm) FROM ANY EDGE. WARRANTY OF ALL
INTERNAL COMPONENTS AND WORKMANSHIP IS VOID IF THE ENCLOSURE
PENETRATIONS DO NOT FOLLOW ALSOENERGY REQUIREMENTS.

3. THIS SYSTEM HAS BEEN DESIGNED TO ALSOENERGY SPECIFICATIONS.

TO PHYSICAL WIRING MAY VOID ENCLOSURE SAFETY CERTIFICATION AND VOID
WARRANTY. MODIFICATIONS TO CONNECTIONS OF COMMUNICATION ENABLED
DEVICE SETTINGS OR CONNECTION LOCATION MAY RESULT IN FAILED
COMMUNICATIONSAND LOST DATA.
4. INTERNAL DEVICES ARE SUPPLIED PRE-WIRED BY ALSOENERGY WITH IP AND
MODBUS ADDRESSING CONFIGURED PER COMMUNICATIONS TABLE.
5. ALL RS485 WIRING SHALL BE IN DAISY CHAIN CONFIGURATION. STUBS SHALL

TERMINATION TYPE.

SHALL BE SC TYPE UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED

PRETERMINATED FIBER JUMPER CABLE OF COMPATIBLE FIBER AND TERMINATION
TYPE. FIBER PATCH CABLE SHALL BE SHIPPED IN ORIGINAL PACKAGING INSIDE
PANEL HOUSING TO PREVENT DAMAGE. ALL FIBER PATCH TERMINATIONS SHALL
BE MADE BY INSTALLER AT COMMISSIONING.
12. MANY ANALOG SENSOR CABLES ARE CALIBRATED. CABLE LENGTH SHALL NOT BE
MODIFIED WITHOUT APPROVAL FROM ALSOENERGY.
13. WIRELESS RADIO CONNECTIONS MUST BE LINE OF SIGHT.
14. ALL ENCLOSURE PENETRATIONS SHALL BE MADE ON THE BOTTOM OF THE
ENCLOSURE GREATER THAN 1" (25mm) FROM ANY EDGE. WARRANTY OF ALL
INTERNAL COMPONENTS AND WORKMANSHIP IS VOID IF THE ENCLOSURE
PENETRATIONS DO NOT FOLLOW ALSOENERGY REQUIREMENTS.

1. ALL WORK SHALL COMPLY WITH APPLICABLE CODE.
2. ALL CURRENT CARRYING CONDUCTORS SHALL BE SIZED WITH CONSIDERATION
FOR MAXIMUM CURRENT, WIRE LENGTH, AND ACCEPTABLE VOLTAGE DROP
3. THIS SYSTEM HAS BEEN DESIGNED TO ALSOENERGY SPECIFICATIONS.
MODIFICATIONS MUST BE APPROVED IN ADVANCE BY ALSOENERGY. CHANGES
TO PHYSICAL WIRING MAY VOID ENCLOSURE SAFETY CERTIFICATION AND VOID
WARRANTY. MODIFICATIONS TO CONNECTIONS OF COMMUNICATION ENABLED
DEVICE SETTINGS OR CONNECTION LOCATION MAY RESULT IN FAILED
COMMUNICATIONSAND LOST DATA.
4. INTERNAL DEVICES ARE SUPPLIED PRE-WIRED BY ALSOENERGY WITH IP AND
MODBUS ADDRESSING CONFIGURED PER COMMUNICATIONS TABLE.
5. ALL RS485 WIRING SHALL BE IN DAISY CHAIN CONFIGURATION. STUBS SHALL
BE LESS THAN 15m (49').
6. SHIELDED CABLE DRAIN SHALL BE CONNECTED TO EARTH GROUND. GROUND
ON ONE END OF CABLE ONLY. GROUND LOOPS MAY RESULT IN FAILED
COMMUNICATION AND LOST DATA.
7. RS-485 CABLE SHALL MEET OR EXCEED BELDEN 3106A SPECIFICATIONS. 4000FT
(1220M) MAX LENGTH PER BUS.
8. ETHERNET NETWORK CABLE (CAT5E or CAT6) SHALL MEET OR EXCEED BELDEN
7919A SPECIFICATIONS, 100m (328') MAX BETWEEN EACH ACTIVE DEVICE.
9. SINGLE MODE FIBER SHALL BE OS2. REFER TO SINGLE LINE DIAGRAM FOR FIBER
TERMINATION TYPE.
10. MULTI-MODE FIBER CABLE SHALL BE 50/125μm OR 62.5/125μm. TERMINATION
SHALL BE SC TYPE UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED
11. ALL FIBER PATCH PANELS PROVIDED BY ALSOENERGY TO INCLUDE ONE
PRETERMINATED FIBER JUMPER CABLE OF COMPATIBLE FIBER AND TERMINATION
TYPE. FIBER PATCH CABLE SHALL BE SHIPPED IN ORIGINAL PACKAGING INSIDE
PANEL HOUSING TO PREVENT DAMAGE. ALL FIBER PATCH TERMINATIONS SHALL
BE MADE BY INSTALLER AT COMMISSIONING.
12. MANY ANALOG SENSOR CABLES ARE CALIBRATED. CABLE LENGTH SHALL NOT BE
MODIFIED WITHOUT APPROVAL FROM ALSOENERGY.
13. WIRELESS RADIO CONNECTIONS MUST BE LINE OF SIGHT.
14. ALL ENCLOSURE PENETRATIONS SHALL BE MADE ON THE BOTTOM OF THE
ENCLOSURE GREATER THAN 1" (25mm) FROM ANY EDGE. WARRANTY OF ALL
INTERNAL COMPONENTS AND WORKMANSHIP IS VOID IF THE ENCLOSURE
PENETRATIONS DO NOT FOLLOW ALSOENERGY REQUIREMENTS.

3. THIS SYSTEM HAS BEEN DESIGNED TO ALSOENERGY SPECIFICATIONS.

BE MADE BY INSTALLER AT COMMISSIONING.

MODIFIED WITHOUT APPROVAL FROM ALSOENERGY.

ENCLOSURE GREATER THAN 1" (25mm) FROM ANY EDGE. WARRANTY OF ALL
INTERNAL COMPONENTS AND WORKMANSHIP IS VOID IF THE ENCLOSURE
PENETRATIONS DO NOT FOLLOW ALSOENERGY REQUIREMENTS.

MODIFICATIONS MUST BE APPROVED IN ADVANCE BY ALSOENERGY. CHANGES | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
TO PHYSICAL WIRING MAY VOID ENCLOSURE SAFETY CERTIFICATION AND VOID | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
WARRANTY. MODIFICATIONS TO CONNECTIONS OF COMMUNICATION ENABLED | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
DEVICE SETTINGS OR CONNECTION LOCATION MAY RESULT IN FAILED | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
COMMUNICATIONSAND LOST DATA. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
4. INTERNAL DEVICES ARE SUPPLIED PRE-WIRED BY ALSOENERGY WITH IP AND | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
MODBUS ADDRESSING CONFIGURED PER COMMUNICATIONS TABLE. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
5. ALL RS485 WIRING SHALL BE IN DAISY CHAIN CONFIGURATION. STUBS SHALL | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
BE LESS THAN 15m (49'). | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
6. SHIELDED CABLE DRAIN SHALL BE CONNECTED TO EARTH GROUND. GROUND | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
ON ONE END OF CABLE ONLY. GROUND LOOPS MAY RESULT IN FAILED | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
COMMUNICATION AND LOST DATA. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
7. RS-485 CABLE SHALL MEET OR EXCEED BELDEN 3106A SPECIFICATIONS. 4000FT | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
(1220M) MAX LENGTH PER BUS. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
8. ETHERNET NETWORK CABLE (CAT5E or CAT6) SHALL MEET OR EXCEED BELDEN | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
7919A SPECIFICATIONS, 100m (328') MAX BETWEEN EACH ACTIVE DEVICE. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
9. SINGLE MODE FIBER SHALL BE OS2. REFER TO SINGLE LINE DIAGRAM FOR FIBER | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
TERMINATION TYPE. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
10. MULTI-MODE FIBER CABLE SHALL BE 50/125μm OR 62.5/125μm. TERMINATION | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
SHALL BE SC TYPE UNLESS OTHERWISE SPECIFIED | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
11. ALL FIBER PATCH PANELS PROVIDED BY ALSOENERGY TO INCLUDE ONE | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
PRETERMINATED FIBER JUMPER CABLE OF COMPATIBLE FIBER AND TERMINATION | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
TYPE. FIBER PATCH CABLE SHALL BE SHIPPED IN ORIGINAL PACKAGING INSIDE | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
PANEL HOUSING TO PREVENT DAMAGE. ALL FIBER PATCH TERMINATIONS SHALL | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
BE MADE BY INSTALLER AT COMMISSIONING. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
12. MANY ANALOG SENSOR CABLES ARE CALIBRATED. CABLE LENGTH SHALL NOT BE | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
MODIFIED WITHOUT APPROVAL FROM ALSOENERGY. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
13. WIRELESS RADIO CONNECTIONS MUST BE LINE OF SIGHT. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
14. ALL ENCLOSURE PENETRATIONS SHALL BE MADE ON THE BOTTOM OF THE | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
ENCLOSURE GREATER THAN 1" (25mm) FROM ANY EDGE. WARRANTY OF ALL | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
INTERNAL COMPONENTS AND WORKMANSHIP IS VOID IF THE ENCLOSURE | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
PENETRATIONS DO NOT FOLLOW ALSOENERGY REQUIREMENTS. | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | | |
